cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.DL

Reasoning: 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on automating the collection and classification of training videos to help job seekers identify and acquire the skills necessary to transition to the next step in their career. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper mentions building a machine learning classifier to predict video relevancy. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as the paper involves natural language processing to extract educational videos. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible category as the paper mentions incorporating embedding vectors associated with the video attributes. 
- cs.DL (Deep Learning) is another possible category as the paper involves building a machine learning classifier and incorporating embedding vectors, which are commonly used in deep learning models.
